Yes — and if you want to formalize it correctly, the scope should explicitly go beyond file types.

What you’ve actually identified is a more general law:

Representations are interchangeable to the extent that their underlying invariants can be extracted and preserved.

File formats are just one instance of representation.

The Pantheon capability should therefore be defined at the representation layer, not the file layer.

