Pantheon Doctrine Extension

Universal Representation Translation (URT) v1.0

Core Principle

All artifacts are representations of underlying structure and meaning.

If the invariant structure can be recovered, it can be re-expressed in any compatible representation.

File formats are only one category of representation.

⸻

Representation Classes

Pantheon should treat representations as belonging to broader classes.

1. Data Representations

Structured information.

Examples:
	•	JSON
	•	YAML
	•	XML
	•	CSV
	•	SQL tables
	•	binary schemas
	•	graph structures

Invariant: entity / relation / value structure

⸻

2. Programmatic Representations

Executable or semi-executable logic.

Examples:
	•	Python code
	•	TypeScript
	•	workflow DAGs
	•	API specifications
	•	smart contracts

Invariant: behavioral rules and state transitions

⸻

3. Document Representations

Human-readable structured knowledge.

Examples:
	•	Markdown
	•	PDF
	•	HTML
	•	design documents
	•	specifications

Invariant: semantic hierarchy and argument structure

⸻

4. Visual Representations

Spatial or graphical encoding of structure.

Examples:
	•	diagrams
	•	charts
	•	UML
	•	flowcharts
	•	knowledge graphs

Invariant: topology and relationships

⸻

5. Narrative Representations

Meaning encoded in story form.

Examples:
	•	case studies
	•	explanations
	•	analogies
	•	doctrine texts

Invariant: causal chain and conceptual mapping

⸻

6. Operational Representations

Instructions for action.

Examples:
	•	checklists
	•	playbooks
	•	workflows
	•	protocols

Invariant: ordered actions with constraints

⸻

The Pantheon Translation Loop

The same loop works for every representation.

Representation A
      ↓
Parse
      ↓
Extract structure
      ↓
Identify semantic invariants
      ↓
Normalize to canonical form
      ↓
Rehydrate
      ↓
Representation B

So a transformation might be:

meeting transcript
    ↓
semantic invariant
    ↓
project plan

or

architecture diagram
    ↓
semantic invariant
    ↓
API schema

or

prose doctrine
    ↓
semantic invariant
    ↓
governance rule set


